\title{Polar form for complex numbers}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[lankham-2016-linear]] 2.3.1}

\p{Let #{z=x+\I y} be a complex number where #{x,y\in\RR}. Then we define the \define{Argument} of #{z} to be the number #{\theta=\Arg(z)} where #{0\leq\theta<2\pi} such that #{x=|z|\cos(\theta)} and #{y=|z|\sin(\theta)}.}

\p{We can also write this in exponential form as #{z=|z|\exp(\I\theta)}.}